### Social Icons (Widget)

Used for a list of social media links.

  * `elType`: `"widget"`
  * `widgetType`: `"social-icons"`
  * `elements`: Must be `[]`.
  * `settings`:
      * `social_icon_list`: An array of objects. Each object needs:
          * `social_icon`: An icon object (e.g., `{ "value": "fab fa-facebook", "library": "fa-brands" }`).
          * `link`: A link object (e.g., `{ "url": "https://facebook.com", ... }`).

**Example (Social Icons):**

```json
{
  "id": "3b2e6cb3",
  "elType": "widget",
  "isInner": false,
  "widgetType": "social-icons",
  "settings": {
    "social_icon_list": [
      {
        "social_icon": { "value": "fab fa-facebook", "library": "fa-brands" },
        "_id": "a22a15d",
        "link": { "url": "https://facebook.com", "is_external": "true", "nofollow": "" }
      },
      {
        "social_icon": { "value": "fab fa-twitter", "library": "fa-brands" },
        "_id": "fcead12",
        "link": { "url": "https://twitter.com", "is_external": "true", "nofollow": "" }
      }
    ],
    "shape": "circle",
    "icon_size": { "unit": "px", "size": 18, "sizes": [] }
  },
  "elements": []
}
```

